I have the honor to acknowledge, herewith, the receipt– Nov. 3, of the shipment of 5 bent wood cain bottom office chairs; 62 yards of carpeting; and one water filter; for use in this Legation; forwarded by J. P. Roosa Esq., United States Despatch Agent, New York; Sept. 27, 1899. Be so kind as to accept my thanks for same. I have the honor to be your obedient servant;
Owen L. W. Smith,
M. R. and C. General.
